Description: CVE-2026-34197 - Prevent VM transport from being used with BrokerView
 Apache ActiveMQ exposes the Jolokia JMX-HTTP bridge with permissive default
 access policies. An authenticated attacker can invoke BrokerService.addConnector()
 or BrokerService.addNetworkConnector() with a malicious discovery URI containing
 the VM transport's brokerConfig parameter to load remote Spring XML contexts,
 enabling arbitrary code execution. This patch adds URI scheme validation to block
 vm:// scheme URIs (including those nested inside composite URIs) in addConnector()
 and addNetworkConnector() JMX operations.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/apache/activemq/commit/0ce7560ca5543d8c0213a23748ae70fc6ec360e8
 upstream, https://github.com/apache/activemq/commit/9bb9ee6fdde5e13c9bfffec19235b8710edcf1e3
Author: Apache ActiveMQ Contributors
Last-Update: 2026-04-17

